# llmwiki — git ignore rules
#
# Goal: commit ONLY framework files. All user data and generated output stays local.

# ─── User data (never committed) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Session transcripts converted from the agent's .jsonl files. These are
# user-specific and often contain personally-identifying information even
# after redaction. Never commit.
raw/sessions/
raw/
!raw/.gitkeep

# LLM-generated wiki pages (Karpathy layer 2). Generated locally from raw/.
# Ignore *contents* rather than the folders themselves so specific
# seed files (_context.md stubs from #60, seeded model entity from
# #55/#56) can be un-ignored via `!` patterns below.
wiki/sources/*
wiki/entities/*
wiki/concepts/*
wiki/syntheses/*
wiki/index.md
wiki/overview.md
wiki/log.md
wiki/lint-report.md
wiki/MEMORY.md
wiki/SOUL.md
wiki/CRITICAL_FACTS.md
wiki/hints.md
wiki/hot.md
wiki/hot/*
!wiki/hot/.gitkeep
wiki/dashboard.md
wiki/categories/*
!wiki/categories/_context.md
!wiki/.gitkeep
!wiki/README.md
# v0.5 (#60): seeded folder-context files ship with the repo so the
# navigation convention is self-documenting.
!wiki/entities/_context.md
!wiki/concepts/_context.md
!wiki/sources/_context.md
!wiki/syntheses/_context.md
!wiki/comparisons/_context.md
!wiki/questions/_context.md
# v0.7 (#55, #56): seeded reference model entity ships with the repo
# so the structured schema + changelog timeline are visible on the
# live demo build.
!wiki/entities/ClaudeSonnet4.md
# v0.7 (#58): second seed model entity so the auto-gen vs-comparison
# pipeline has a real pair to render on the demo build.
!wiki/entities/GPT5.md
# Project topics (v0.9): `wiki/projects/<slug>.md` is hand-curated
# per-project metadata (topics, description, homepage). Small, stable,
# user-curated — committed so the demo build ships with topic chips
# on every project card. Users can add their own project profiles
# and they'll be picked up automatically.
!wiki/projects/

# Generated static HTML site (Karpathy layer 3).
site/
site-html/
dist-site/
!site/.gitkeep

# Converter state — tracks mtimes to avoid re-processing unchanged files.
.ingestion-state.json
.llmwiki-state.json
.llmwiki-synth-state.json
.llmwiki-queue.json
.llmwiki-dream-state.json
.llmwiki-batch-state.json

# v1.0 (#160): multi-agent skill mirrors are derived from .claude/skills/
# by `llmwiki install-skills`. The canonical source ships with the repo;
# the mirrors are regenerated locally and don't need to be committed.
.codex/skills/
.agents/skills/

# Local config (user-specific).
config.json
config.local.json
.env
.env.local

# Logs
*.log
/tmp/llmwiki-*.log

# ─── Python ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
share/python-wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg
MANIFEST
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/
.tox/

# ─── Editors & OS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ─── Claude Code / agent local state ──────────────────────────────────────
# NEVER commit .claude/ or .codex/ LOCAL settings (they leak machine paths).
# We DO commit .claude/commands/ and .claude/skills/ (framework-level).
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/projects/
.claude/cache/
.codex/sessions/
.codex/cache/

# ─── Marketing playbook (local planning doc, not committed) ──────────────
_marketing-playbook.md

# ─── Personal framework reference (local-only) ───────────────────────────
# Pratiyush's Open Source Framework v4.0 notes — kept here for reference
# while building but NOT committed (personal process docs).
.framework/

# ─── Research corpus (local-only) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Cloned reference implementations for Phase 1.25 Research. Pulled from
# Karpathy's gist and related searches. Never committed — respect upstream
# licenses and keep the repo lean.
.temp/
.research/

# ─── Knowledge graph output (v0.2+) ───────────────────────────────────────
# graph/graph.json and graph.html are generated by 'llmwiki graph'.
# Local output, not committed.
graph/
!graph/.gitkeep

# ─── Eval reports (v0.3+) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Generated by 'llmwiki eval' — tracked locally for CI baselines, not commited.
eval-report.json

# ─── E2E screenshot artifacts (v0.9, #45) ────────────────────────────────
# Playwright + pytest-bdd produces per-breakpoint screenshots for
# visual regression. Committed baselines would explode the repo; CI
# uploads them as workflow artifacts instead.
tests/e2e/screenshots/
test-results/
playwright-report/
.claude/worktrees/
gaps.md
